There are parts of this that I'm not happy with, but wasn't sure exactly how or what I should change. I debated changing it around so that it wasn't on the loose. In that case, I envisioned the Foundation giving it different materials to see what it created, which would demand a test log. While I like SCPs like this most of the time, I didn't really want to go that far against my original vision, so I didn't do the re-write. I'm perfectly open to criticisms, suggestions, and edits.

UPDATE: I proofread the entire thing again, and made quite a few changes throughout in terms of sentence structure, tone, and grammar. I'm hoping this is at least a good step in bringing up the writing quality of the article. Please let me know if I messed anything up, or if it is still lacking.





