I can understand that, and I didn't set out to make a Keter class object for my first SCP. However, I ended up deciding that I didn't want to make another SCP that . I preferred the idea that the creations showed up randomly and unexpectedly, making the SCP's creation process a complete mystery. The fact that it's Keter and on the loose was actually just the logical route I felt it needed to go to to get the idea across the way I wanted it to, not the other way around (if that makes sense).

Tone is something I really struggled with for my first real entry, as I am still very inexperienced. Despite having read hundreds of SCPs, I still couldn't quite grasp it the way others have. Any suggestions in that department would be greatly appreciated.







